ZH: 请不要扣我的扣子，谢谢。
EN: Please do not button up my buttons, thank you.

ZH: 这件外套有扣子是因为它是冬天的外套。
EN: This jacket has buttons because it is a winter jacket.

ZH: 我总是忘记扣安全带。
EN: I always forget to fasten my seatbelt.

ZH: 她用力扣着钢笔的笔盖。
EN: She securely fastened the cap of the pen.

ZH: 把那颗钮扣扣上去吧。
EN: Button up that button.

ZH: 他扣住了我的手腕。
EN: He grabbed my wrist.

ZH: 我的胃疼得像有人用钳子扣住一样。
EN: My stomach hurt as if someone was grasping it with pliers.

ZH: 她把头发扣起来让空气流通。
EN: She tied up her hair to allow for air circulation.

ZH: 他用力扣住了门把手。
EN: He firmly held onto the door handle.

ZH: 请确保每个扣子都已经扣好。
EN: Please make sure that all buttons are properly fastened.

ZH: 学生们被要求扣好制服的扣子。
EN: Students were asked to fasten the buttons on their uniforms.

ZH: 他把领带扣好，准备去参加会议。
EN: He fixed his tie, ready to attend the meeting.

ZH: 她喜欢扣着球帽的帽檐。
EN: She likes to adjust the brim of her baseball cap.

ZH: 请扣好自行车头盔，做好安全准备。
EN: Please fasten your bicycle helmet securely for safety.

ZH: 请扣好座椅安全带以确保安全。
EN: Please buckle up your seat belt for safety.

ZH: 手表的金属扣子已经生锈了。
EN: The metal buckle of the watch has rusted.

ZH: 她把布丁扣在了她的钥匙链上。
EN: She attached the pudding to her keychain.

ZH: 请扣好窗帘，避免阳光进入房间。
EN: Please fasten the curtains to prevent sunlight from entering the room.

ZH: 他用力扣紧鞋带，准备出门。
EN: He tied his shoelaces tightly, ready to go out.

ZH: 妈妈叮嘱我扣好大衣的纽扣。
EN: Mom reminded me to button up my coat.
